# Lean Canvas: {{NAME}}

> A 9-block lean canvas (Ash Maurya). Optional context layer between Vision and Functional.
> Problem-first — fill in Problem and Customer Segments before Solution. Validates business viability before committing to features.

---

## Problem
<!-- Top 1-3 problems your customers have today. Be specific. What's broken or missing in their current workflow? -->

## Customer Segments
<!-- Who has this problem? Early adopters first (the ones who feel it most). What identifies them? -->

## Unique Value Proposition
<!-- Single, clear, compelling message: why are you different and worth paying attention to? -->

## Solution
<!-- Top 1-3 features that address the top 1-3 problems. -->

## Channels
<!-- Path to customers: how do they hear about you, how do you reach them? -->

## Revenue Streams
<!-- How does this make money? Pricing model, transaction value, lifetime value. -->

## Cost Structure
<!-- Customer acquisition cost, infrastructure, salaries, fixed vs variable costs. -->

## Key Metrics
<!-- The 3-5 numbers that tell you whether this is working. -->

## Unfair Advantage
<!-- Something that can't easily be bought or copied. Network effects, deep domain expertise, exclusive partnerships. -->

